#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Howto Update FusionInventory Agent through a deployment task"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The basic problem with updating the agent through a deployment task is the "
"agent will have to uninstall itself while in use, thus throwing some errors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"A good method to update the agent without errors is to create a scheduled "
"task that will update the agent to it's latest version onboot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Let's first create a fusioninventory SFX package containing both x64 and x86 "
"versions, and that maybe used to install a new agent or update an existing "
"one, regardless of the architecture."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You'll need the latest stable version of 7zSD SFX that you can get "
"[here](http://7zsfx.info/en/).  The file 7zSD.sfx needs to be ressource "
"hacked so it will ask for UAC privileges when executed.  You may find all "
"necessary files (pre-ressource hacked) and scripts "
"[here](http://www.netpower.fr)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Basically we'll create a SFX package containing the following three files: * "
"* fusioninventory-agent_windows-x86_x.yy.zz.exe * "
"* fusioninventory-agent_windows-x64_x.yy.zz.exe * install.cmd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The install.cmd script will contain all the necessary information to install "
"/ update a FusionInventory Agent (see below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You'll have to create a 7zip archive of those three files with the following "
"command (providing you already have 7z.exe):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ..\\7z a -r FUSIONINV.7z *.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The archive has to be linked together with the SFX module and a SFX "
"configuration file.  We'll create a config file named sfx_config.txt and "
"containing the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ;!@Install@!UTF-8!\n"
"    Title=\"Installation FusionInventory\"\n"
"    RunProgram=\"x86:install.cmd\" \n"
"    RunProgram=\"x64:install.cmd\" \n"
"    SelfDelete=\"1\"\n"
"    ;!@InstallEnd@!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Then we can create the package with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    copy /b 7zSD.sfx + sfx_config.txt + FUSIONINV.7z FUSIONINV.EXE\n"
msgstr ""
